rationale:
Choice C is correct. If a value of x  satisfies f(x)=0, the graph of y=fx will contain a point x,0 and thus touch the x-axis. Since there are 3 points at which this graph touches the x-axis, there are 3 values of x for which f(x)=0.

Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.
